Subject: [PATCH] =?UTF-8?q?Activate=20GPEC2A=20File-Unlock=20=E2=80=94=20r?=
 =?UTF-8?q?ecover=20real=20patterns=20from=20a=20genuine=20unlock?=
MIME-Version: 1.0
Content-Type: text/plain; charset=UTF-8
Content-Transfer-Encoding: 8bit

The WinLicense-sealed unlock patterns were never statically extractable, so the
GPEC2A File-Unlock tab was inert (PATTERNS_AVAILABLE=false). Recovered them by
byte-diffing a real locked/unlocked INT_FLASH pair (derive-gpec-patterns.mjs):

  UNLOCK_TARGET_PATTERN    = [0xE6,0x06,0x65,0xDD]   (byte[match] -> 0xE8)
  ALREADY_UNLOCKED_PATTERN = [0x06,0x65,0xDD,0xE8]
  UNLOCK_FLAG_OFFSET       = 0x2FFF0   (CORRECTED — the IL guess 0x2FFFC was
                                        unchanged in the real unlock)

PROVEN: patchGpec2aFile() applied to the real locked file reproduces the real
unlocked file BYTE-FOR-BYTE (0 diffs). The pattern occurs exactly once in every
4 MB INT_FLASH dump in the corpus (universal firmware code, not dump-specific),
so the fixture test now performs a genuine no-opts unlock and asserts exactly 2
bytes change + idempotency.

Scope: INT_FLASH only. EXT_EEPROM lacks this pattern (resolves to offset_only) —
needs its own locked/unlocked pair. GEN_DETECT still null (label only).
NOTE: these are algorithm constants (firmware search patterns), not vehicle data.

Tests updated for the activated state (PATTERNS_AVAILABLE=true, 0x2FFF0).
